Homepage: http://www.amirifont.org
Description: Arabic Naskh style typographically oriented font
 Amiri is a classical Arabic typeface in Naskh style for typesetting
 books and other running text.
 .
 Its design is a revival of the beautiful typeface pioneered in early
 20th century by Bulaq Press in Cairo, also known as Amiria Press, after
 which the font is named.
 .
 Amiri font covers the full Unicode 6.0 Arabic and Arabic Supplement
 blocks, as well as the compatibility Arabic Presentation Forms-A and B
 blocks.
